1
00:00:18,977 --> 00:00:20,728
I'm so scared.

2
00:00:20,729 --> 00:00:22,021
I don't like this.

3
00:00:22,022 --> 00:00:24,356
I HATE IT

4
00:00:24,357 --> 00:00:26,317
- I'm so scared.
- Are you okay?

5
00:00:27,110 --> 00:00:28,986
We've reached Baeksudam Garden.

6
00:00:28,987 --> 00:00:30,446
ARRIVED AT BAEKSUDAM GARDEN

7
00:00:30,447 --> 00:00:31,947
I'll park just up here.

8
00:00:31,948 --> 00:00:33,533
ARRIVED AT BAEKSUDAM GARDEN

9
00:00:34,576 --> 00:00:35,826
I really don't want to get out.

10
00:00:35,827 --> 00:00:37,828
Was it a restaurant?

11
00:00:37,829 --> 00:00:39,163
- You mean in the past?
- Yes.

12
00:00:39,164 --> 00:00:41,541
- It looks like a chicken soup restaurant.
- It does.

13
00:00:42,375 --> 00:00:43,751
BAEKSUDAM GARDEN

14
00:00:43,752 --> 00:00:46,962
A BUILDING ABANDONED LONG AGO

15
00:00:46,963 --> 00:00:48,255
- Should we go in?
- Yes.

16
00:00:48,256 --> 00:00:49,174
No.

17
00:00:50,592 --> 00:00:51,759
Let's go.

18
00:00:51,760 --> 00:00:53,510
I'm too scared to even feel the heat.

19
00:00:53,511 --> 00:00:54,636
I'm cold.

20
00:00:54,637 --> 00:00:56,513
- You're cold?
- It really is cold.

21
00:00:56,514 --> 00:00:58,849
It's currently 35 degrees Celsius.

22
00:00:58,850 --> 00:00:59,975
I'm really struggling.

23
00:00:59,976 --> 00:01:04,021
We should be extra careful, guys.

24
00:01:04,022 --> 00:01:06,940
- It's a bed and breakfast.
- Yes, it is.

25
00:01:06,941 --> 00:01:09,277
It says, "Fishing gear, Baeksudam Garden."

26
00:01:10,028 --> 00:01:12,571
- This area's been closed off.
- Yong-jin.

27
00:01:12,572 --> 00:01:13,822
YONG-JIN SEEMS DRAWN TO SOMETHING

28
00:01:13,823 --> 00:01:15,741
Look at the reservoir.

29
00:01:15,742 --> 00:01:16,700
BAEKSUDAM GARDEN

30
00:01:16,701 --> 00:01:20,287
BAEKSUDAM GARDEN OVERLOOKS THE RESERVOIR

31
00:01:20,288 --> 00:01:22,039
<i>We arrived at Baeksudam Garden,</i>

32
00:01:22,040 --> 00:01:25,084
and we could clearly see the reservoir.

33
00:01:25,085 --> 00:01:28,587
<i>There was a fog over the water.</i>

34
00:01:28,588 --> 00:01:30,547
<i>And the water was really dark.</i>

35
00:01:30,548 --> 00:01:34,426
I knew from that moment
that things were about to get real.

36
00:01:34,427 --> 00:01:36,386
Things were about to go down.

37
00:01:36,387 --> 00:01:39,640
Let's go into Baeksudam Garden, everyone.

38
00:01:39,641 --> 00:01:41,850
"Bed and breakfast, fishing gear."

39
00:01:41,851 --> 00:01:42,935
There's a spider.

40
00:01:42,936 --> 00:01:48,024
You can tell this area's been abandoned
because it's covered in cobwebs.

41
00:01:51,861 --> 00:01:54,030
THE AGENTS ENTER CAUTIOUSLY

42
00:01:56,074 --> 00:01:57,491
Do-hoon, it's what you wanted.

43
00:01:57,492 --> 00:01:58,408
FLASHLIGHT OBTAINED

44
00:01:58,409 --> 00:01:59,660
Yes, this is great.

45
00:01:59,661 --> 00:02:00,954
We really need it.

46
00:02:02,413 --> 00:02:03,248
Let's go.

47
00:02:03,832 --> 00:02:04,916
Is it open?

48
00:02:07,377 --> 00:02:08,586
FOOD STORAGE

49
00:02:09,963 --> 00:02:12,257
This place is the real deal.

50
00:02:13,758 --> 00:02:15,009
It's the real deal, guys.

51
00:02:17,637 --> 00:02:18,929
- Hold on.
- That's better.

52
00:02:18,930 --> 00:02:20,389
Oh, it was a restaurant.

53
00:02:20,390 --> 00:02:22,558
It was a proper restaurant.

54
00:02:22,559 --> 00:02:26,271
BAEKSUDAM GARDEN

55
00:02:26,855 --> 00:02:29,857
<i>It seemed like it had been
abandoned for ages.</i>

56
00:02:29,858 --> 00:02:32,401
<i>There were cobwebs everywhere.</i>

57
00:02:32,402 --> 00:02:35,320
<i>All the objects were really old.</i>

58
00:02:35,321 --> 00:02:40,368
You could tell no one had
been in that restaurant for years.

59
00:02:43,121 --> 00:02:44,788
What was that sound?

60
00:02:44,789 --> 00:02:46,123
It's like a coffee vending machine.

61
00:02:46,124 --> 00:02:47,207
The dispenser is running.

62
00:02:47,208 --> 00:02:48,917
It's pouring coffee!

63
00:02:48,918 --> 00:02:52,379
THE COFFEE VENDING MACHINE
TURNED ON SUDDENLY

64
00:02:52,380 --> 00:02:54,464
- Why did it suddenly do that?
- Why is it running?

65
00:02:54,465 --> 00:02:56,676
- I hate this.
- The machine is running?

66
00:02:57,677 --> 00:02:58,760
Why is it running?

67
00:02:58,761 --> 00:03:00,429
- I hate this.
- Unbelievable.

68
00:03:00,430 --> 00:03:02,222
Is it black liquid again?

69
00:03:02,223 --> 00:03:03,181
It's really hot.

70
00:03:03,182 --> 00:03:04,474
- No, it's just coffee.
- Really?

71
00:03:04,475 --> 00:03:06,853
- It's really coffee.
- Did someone turn it on and run?

72
00:03:07,353 --> 00:03:08,770
- It's going again.
- It's a second cup.

73
00:03:08,771 --> 00:03:10,731
ONE MORE CUP

74
00:03:10,732 --> 00:03:11,982
Did someone press it?

75
00:03:11,983 --> 00:03:13,150
I hate this.

76
00:03:13,151 --> 00:03:14,943
But look at all these cobwebs.

77
00:03:14,944 --> 00:03:18,113
We'd better not drink this.

78
00:03:18,114 --> 00:03:19,448
IT LOOKS DANGEROUS TO DRINK

79
00:03:19,449 --> 00:03:20,532
This is strange.

80
00:03:20,533 --> 00:03:22,409
It's like someone's trying
to make us drink it.

81
00:03:22,410 --> 00:03:23,493
It feels like a trap.

82
00:03:23,494 --> 00:03:24,537
Let's not drink it.

83
00:03:34,464 --> 00:03:35,631
Wait.

84
00:03:35,632 --> 00:03:36,591
What's up?

85
00:03:38,092 --> 00:03:40,219
You can tell someone's been living here.

86
00:03:40,220 --> 00:03:42,262
- Really?
- Let's go in and look.

87
00:03:42,263 --> 00:03:43,306
What is this place?

88
00:03:46,476 --> 00:03:48,228
- What's with the equipment?
- This is…

89
00:03:48,853 --> 00:03:52,814
<i>In the room,
a tent stood beside a table with a laptop.</i>

90
00:03:52,815 --> 00:03:55,442
<i>There was also filming equipment.</i>

91
00:03:55,443 --> 00:03:59,696
It seemed like someone
had been residing here for a while.

92
00:03:59,697 --> 00:04:02,115
These are traces of someone
who's lived here.

93
00:04:02,116 --> 00:04:03,116
Could that be him?

94
00:04:03,117 --> 00:04:04,618
- It could be.
- I think you're right.

95
00:04:04,619 --> 00:04:05,869
Was it King MS?

96
00:04:05,870 --> 00:04:07,746
"It's me, Oh Deok-u. I emailed you."

97
00:04:07,747 --> 00:04:10,666
"Is this the right chat? I'm a real fan."

98
00:04:10,667 --> 00:04:12,000
- MS.
- King MS.

99
00:04:12,001 --> 00:04:13,001
It is him!

100
00:04:13,002 --> 00:04:14,920
- He slept here?
- It's definitely him.

101
00:04:14,921 --> 00:04:17,005
ZERO-FEAR MU-SEONG TV

102
00:04:17,006 --> 00:04:18,382
MS must stand for Mu-seong.

103
00:04:18,383 --> 00:04:19,549
- It's Mu-seong.
- I see.

104
00:04:19,550 --> 00:04:21,051
- He was a YouTuber.
- "King Mu-seong."

105
00:04:21,052 --> 00:04:23,303
That's why Deok-u said he was a fan.

106
00:04:23,304 --> 00:04:25,013
- Do we need to unlock it too?
- Should we try?

107
00:04:25,014 --> 00:04:26,182
It's the Baeksudam Garden key.

108
00:04:26,766 --> 00:04:28,351
This is the key to the garden.

109
00:04:29,060 --> 00:04:31,103
It's locked with a password.

110
00:04:31,104 --> 00:04:33,772
- The password hint is "NO."
- "No."

111
00:04:33,773 --> 00:04:35,024
Is it short for "number"?

112
00:04:37,151 --> 00:04:38,569
Why is it "No"?

113
00:04:39,279 --> 00:04:40,779
Let's look for a clue.

114
00:04:40,780 --> 00:04:41,948
I'm really scared.

115
00:04:43,741 --> 00:04:44,951
I found clothes.

116
00:04:45,576 --> 00:04:46,702
A BAG OF MU-SEONG TV MERCHANDISE

117
00:04:46,703 --> 00:04:47,619
There are clothes and…

118
00:04:47,620 --> 00:04:49,454
It says "No news is…"

119
00:04:49,455 --> 00:04:50,998
"Good news."

120
00:04:50,999 --> 00:04:52,333
It says "no fear."

121
00:04:53,459 --> 00:04:55,877
- That must be it.
- Let's type in "fear."

122
00:04:55,878 --> 00:04:58,923
ENTERING "FEAR" STRAIGHT AWAY

123
00:04:59,424 --> 00:05:00,340
It worked.

124
00:05:00,341 --> 00:05:01,759
We did it!

125
00:05:03,511 --> 00:05:05,721
- It's a YouTube page.
- Yes.

126
00:05:05,722 --> 00:05:07,556
My goodness. There are videos.

127
00:05:07,557 --> 00:05:08,808
- There are videos.
- Oh, gosh.

128
00:05:09,392 --> 00:05:11,268
- Should we watch them in order?
- Yes.

129
00:05:11,269 --> 00:05:12,853
I'm scared.

130
00:05:12,854 --> 00:05:13,854
A NEW BEGINNING

131
00:05:13,855 --> 00:05:15,522
CLICKING ON THE FIRST VIDEO

132
00:05:15,523 --> 00:05:17,233
<i>Ahn Mu-seong's Unsung Ghosts.</i>

133
00:05:17,859 --> 00:05:19,735
- Is that his catchphrase?
- Yes.

134
00:05:19,736 --> 00:05:22,154
<i>I'm Ahn Mu-seong of Zero-fear Mu-seong TV.</i>

135
00:05:22,155 --> 00:05:23,196
<i>It's been a while.</i>

136
00:05:23,197 --> 00:05:24,698
Why is he speaking like this?

137
00:05:24,699 --> 00:05:26,241
- It seems like an apology video.
- It does.

138
00:05:26,242 --> 00:05:28,577
<i>-It's been six months since my last video.</i>
- You're right.

139
00:05:28,578 --> 00:05:29,786
Is it a comeback video?

140
00:05:29,787 --> 00:05:31,538
- I think so.
<i>- It feels awkward</i>

141
00:05:31,539 --> 00:05:33,499
<i>to address you all so formally.</i>

142
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,376
<i>I self-reflected for a long time.</i>

143
00:05:36,377 --> 00:05:37,961
- What did he do?
<i>- I want to address</i>

144
00:05:37,962 --> 00:05:39,838
<i>-the altered video scandal.</i>
- He altered them.

145
00:05:39,839 --> 00:05:41,590
Why did he do that?

146
00:05:41,591 --> 00:05:43,634
<i>I'm sorry again for causing distress.</i>

147
00:05:46,220 --> 00:05:48,346
<i>For those of you who waited
for me to come back,</i>

148
00:05:48,347 --> 00:05:50,557
<i>I promise to return the favor
like The Grateful Magpie.</i>

149
00:05:50,558 --> 00:05:52,142
<i>Squawk!</i>

150
00:05:52,143 --> 00:05:53,852
That sounds more like a crow.

151
00:05:53,853 --> 00:05:54,978
GIGGLING

152
00:05:54,979 --> 00:05:56,730
<i>To prove my remorse,</i>

153
00:05:56,731 --> 00:05:58,940
<i>I deleted all my past videos.</i>

154
00:05:58,941 --> 00:06:00,067
No wonder there are so few.

155
00:06:00,068 --> 00:06:01,526
<i>I'm speaking to you as the real me.</i>

156
00:06:01,527 --> 00:06:03,279
<i>There is something I must tell you.</i>

157
00:06:03,780 --> 00:06:05,363
<i>My Little Scaredy-cats…</i>

158
00:06:05,364 --> 00:06:06,740
- "Scaredy-cat"? Me?
- Yes?

159
00:06:06,741 --> 00:06:08,200
<i>Have you ever walked past</i>

160
00:06:08,201 --> 00:06:10,494
<i>-a chilling abandoned building?</i>
- This is what he does.

161
00:06:10,495 --> 00:06:12,037
<i>And were too scared to go in?</i>

162
00:06:12,038 --> 00:06:13,997
<i>Don't get scared, and reach out to me.</i>

163
00:06:13,998 --> 00:06:16,583
- That's what Deok-u did.
- He reached out to him.

164
00:06:16,584 --> 00:06:20,045
<i>- I'll return next Monday with new content.</i>
- Monday?

165
00:06:20,046 --> 00:06:21,838
<i>Squawk!</i>

166
00:06:21,839 --> 00:06:23,799
There were two more videos.

167
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:24,841
- I'll click this one.
- Okay.

168
00:06:24,842 --> 00:06:25,926
He uploaded it two weeks ago.

169
00:06:25,927 --> 00:06:28,596
<i>Ahn Mu-seong's Unsung Ghosts.</i>

170
00:06:29,097 --> 00:06:31,556
<i>Welcome to Zero-fear Mu-seong TV.</i>

171
00:06:31,557 --> 00:06:33,059
<i>Hey, Little Scaredy-cats.</i>

172
00:06:33,559 --> 00:06:36,103
<i>-I'm at an abandoned temple.</i>
- A temple?

173
00:06:36,104 --> 00:06:37,229
SWIVELS

174
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:38,815
I'm scared.

175
00:06:42,068 --> 00:06:43,569
<i>I've never seen so much mold.</i>

176
00:06:44,195 --> 00:06:46,948
<i>I think there's a water vein here.</i>

177
00:06:48,741 --> 00:06:49,783
It's so chilling.

178
00:06:49,784 --> 00:06:51,243
This kind of thing scares me.

179
00:06:51,244 --> 00:06:52,995
<i>It's giving me the creeps.</i>

180
00:06:56,249 --> 00:06:57,249
Breathe, Do-hoon.

181
00:06:57,250 --> 00:06:59,001
- Remember to breathe.
- I am breathing.

182
00:06:59,544 --> 00:07:00,752
Deep breath, Do-hoon.

183
00:07:00,753 --> 00:07:03,339
LET'S ALL BREATHE TOGETHER

184
00:07:05,633 --> 00:07:07,425
<i>I'm entering a new space.</i>

185
00:07:07,426 --> 00:07:09,595
<i>This place is a mess.</i>

186
00:07:10,346 --> 00:07:11,848
<i>-What's that?</i>
- What happened?

187
00:07:12,348 --> 00:07:13,306
What's going on?

188
00:07:13,307 --> 00:07:14,224
<i>Stop following me!</i>

189
00:07:14,225 --> 00:07:16,101
<i>-What the heck?</i>
- What's happening?

190
00:07:16,102 --> 00:07:17,603
COVERING HIS EYES BY INSTINCT

191
00:07:18,646 --> 00:07:20,397
THE VIDEO JUST CUT OFF

192
00:07:20,398 --> 00:07:21,357
What?

193
00:07:23,109 --> 00:07:24,109
- I'll press play.
- Okay.

194
00:07:24,110 --> 00:07:25,527
This video is from 12 days ago.

195
00:07:25,528 --> 00:07:28,905
<i>Ahn Mu-seong's Unsung Ghosts.</i>

196
00:07:28,906 --> 00:07:31,700
This is the last video
before he went missing.

197
00:07:31,701 --> 00:07:32,535
That's right.

198
00:07:33,911 --> 00:07:35,996
<i>According to the local villagers…</i>

199
00:07:35,997 --> 00:07:37,331
<i>I hate this so much.</i>

200
00:07:37,915 --> 00:07:40,208
<i>…this place keeps changing hands
because of the ghosts.</i>

201
00:07:40,209 --> 00:07:41,127
SECOND CHILLING ABANDONED BUILDING

202
00:07:44,380 --> 00:07:46,131
If you film content like this,

203
00:07:46,132 --> 00:07:48,300
shouldn't an ambulance be on stand-by?

204
00:07:48,301 --> 00:07:49,802
You also need the special forces.

205
00:07:50,428 --> 00:07:51,888
<i>I'm going in.</i>

206
00:07:52,972 --> 00:07:54,973
<i>-Here I go.
- It's in shambles.</i>

207
00:07:54,974 --> 00:07:55,891
What on earth?

208
00:07:55,892 --> 00:07:57,392
<i>I came here alone.</i>

209
00:07:57,393 --> 00:07:59,895
<i>Why do I feel like I'm not alone?</i>

210
00:07:59,896 --> 00:08:00,937
You're probably not alone.

211
00:08:00,938 --> 00:08:03,064
<i>Why do I feel like someone's watching me?</i>

212
00:08:03,065 --> 00:08:04,692
Someone probably is watching.

213
00:08:06,277 --> 00:08:07,277
That's how it goes.

214
00:08:07,278 --> 00:08:09,237
<i>Stop hiding and get out here, you rascals!</i>

215
00:08:09,238 --> 00:08:11,282
<i>Ahn Mu-seong's Unsung Ghosts.</i>

216
00:08:12,325 --> 00:08:14,242
- He seems very afraid.
- Right?

217
00:08:14,243 --> 00:08:15,577
He seems terrified.

218
00:08:15,578 --> 00:08:17,579
- He fears everything.
- He's the king of fear.

219
00:08:17,580 --> 00:08:18,915
He's crapping his pants.

220
00:08:19,582 --> 00:08:20,625
That's funny.

221
00:08:22,835 --> 00:08:25,253
<i>Why is this hole here?</i>

222
00:08:25,254 --> 00:08:27,048
<i>Someone must have carved it out.</i>

223
00:08:27,632 --> 00:08:28,548
Don't tell me…

224
00:08:28,549 --> 00:08:30,384
How far will your curiosity lead you?

225
00:08:33,179 --> 00:08:34,305
What was that?

226
00:08:35,264 --> 00:08:37,140
IT'S HAIR-RAISINGLY SCARY

227
00:08:37,141 --> 00:08:39,226
It's scarier that nothing is happening.

228
00:08:39,227 --> 00:08:40,644
You're not kidding.

229
00:08:40,645 --> 00:08:41,604
The suspense is unreal.

230
00:08:42,605 --> 00:08:44,231
<i>I can't stay any longer. I'm leaving!</i>

231
00:08:44,232 --> 00:08:45,148
HE'S THE MOST AFRAID

232
00:08:45,149 --> 00:08:47,484
AHN MU-SEONG RUNNING AWAY

233
00:08:47,485 --> 00:08:49,528
END OF VIDEO

234
00:08:49,529 --> 00:08:50,988
That's how it ends?

235
00:08:51,489 --> 00:08:53,990
I think that's his trademark.

236
00:08:53,991 --> 00:08:55,075
It seems like it.

237
00:08:55,076 --> 00:08:56,743
Let's look for more videos.

238
00:08:56,744 --> 00:08:57,869
- Others?
- Yes.

239
00:08:57,870 --> 00:09:00,747
I think there was a livestream.

240
00:09:00,748 --> 00:09:03,124
I bet he did a lot of livestreams.

241
00:09:03,125 --> 00:09:04,501
I think there is one.

242
00:09:04,502 --> 00:09:05,794
- Here it is.
- It was live?

243
00:09:05,795 --> 00:09:06,795
You found it?

244
00:09:06,796 --> 00:09:08,588
There's a real-time livestream.

245
00:09:08,589 --> 00:09:09,798
- Right now?
- It was last week.

246
00:09:09,799 --> 00:09:11,342
Oh, I see. I got chills for a second.

247
00:09:11,884 --> 00:09:14,678
THE LAST VIDEO BEFORE HE WENT OFF RADAR

248
00:09:14,679 --> 00:09:17,347
<i>Hello, it's me. Little Scaredy-cats.</i>

249
00:09:17,348 --> 00:09:18,932
This wasn't pre-recorded.

250
00:09:18,933 --> 00:09:19,891
- Yes.
- It's not subtitled.

251
00:09:19,892 --> 00:09:22,477
